    "version": "0.1",
    "units_length": "Metre",
    "author": "OpenLoco Contributors",
    "description": "Mini-Whegs with obstacle-aware gait modulation. Mechanical layer identical to `mini_whegs.udd.json` (same 5 links / 4 joints / 4 actuator slots, same mesh hashes). The superset adds: (1) a forward-facing depth sensor on the chassis, (2) a classical `obstacle_height` skill consuming it, (3) a second `cautious` mode with a ~50 % velocity cap on the wheg drives, and (4) two skill-graph transitions with hysteresis — `normal → cautious` when the obstacle ahead exceeds 0.030 m (spoke-climbability threshold for the 0.045 m spoke length), and `cautious → normal` when the path clears below 0.010 m. First descriptor exercising a transition on a classical-CV skill output; complements the M4 autonomous descriptor's VLM-driven transitions.",
    "generator": "openloco-cli"
  },
